main event: A UFO sighting was reported by a military source in Condon, Oregon, in July 1966 involving one ground vessel observed for 12 to 20 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as star-shaped and white,The sighting occurred near Condon AFS, with conditions being mostly clear,The observer noted the object appeared to move rapidly and then turn suddenly,The report was filed by AIC Joel C. Snider of the 636th Radar Station and coordinated by Colonel Warren S. Winkler of USAF,There were no photographs or physical evidence presented.
witness description: Joel C. Snider, AIC, 636th Radar Station
